---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Contribute to Claudient — add a skill, agent, or hook"
  description="Every Claudient skill lives in one markdown file. Learn how to write and submit a skill, agent, or hook via a standard GitHub PR."
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="container-page py-20 md:py-28">
    <div class="max-w-3xl">
      <p class="pill mb-6">Open source · MIT</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-6xl font-semibold tracking-tight leading-[1.05]">
        Add a skill. Get it in front of thousands.
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-6 text-lg md:text-xl max-w-2xl" style="color: var(--color-muted);">
        Claudient is community-powered. Every skill is one markdown file. If it made
        Claude Code meaningfully better for you, it belongs here.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-8 flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-3">
        <a
          href="https://github.com/Claudients/Claudient"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener"
          class="btn-primary"
        >
          Fork on GitHub
        </a>
        <a href="/guides/skill-authoring/" class="btn-ghost">Skill authoring guide</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What to contribute -->
  <section
    class="border-y"
    style="background-color: var(--color-bg-elevated); border-color: var(--color-border);"
  >
    <div class="container-page py-16">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight mb-8">What you can contribute</h2>
      <div class="grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3">
        {[
          { type: "Skill", path: "skills/<category>/", desc: "A slash command that activates domain-specific behavior in Claude Code." },
          { type: "Agent", path: "agents/<category>/", desc: "A specialist subagent definition — model guidance, tool restrictions, trigger conditions." },
          { type: "Hook", path: "hooks/<trigger>/", desc: "An event-driven automation that runs outside Claude's context as a real shell process." },
          { type: "Rule", path: "rules/", desc: "An always-follow guideline that shapes Claude's behavior throughout a session." },
          { type: "Workflow", path: "workflows/", desc: "An end-to-end multi-step process — how Claude should handle a complex task." },
          { type: "Guide", path: "guides/", desc: "A deep-dive documentation piece on a Claude Code feature or pattern." },
          { type: "Translation", path: "guides/<lang>/", desc: "A translated version of any existing English file (FR, DE, NL, ES)." },
        ].map((item) => (
          <div class="card p-5">
            <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-2">
              <span class="font-semibold text-sm">{item.type}</span>
              <code
                class="text-xs font-mono px-2 py-0.5 rounded"
                style="background-color: var(--color-muted-bg); color: var(--color-muted);"
              >
                {item.path}
              </code>
            </div>
            <p class="text-sm" style="color: var(--color-muted);">{item.desc}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Skill format -->
  <section class="container-page py-16">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight mb-3">Skill file format</h2>
    <p class="mb-8 text-sm max-w-2xl" style="color: var(--color-muted);">
      Every file in <code class="text-xs px-1 py-0.5 rounded" style="background-color: var(--color-muted-bg);">skills/</code> must follow this four-section structure exactly.
      Do not add sections beyond this without a clear reason.
    </p>
    <div
      class="rounded-lg p-6"
      style="background-color: var(--color-muted-bg); border: 1px solid var(--color-border);"
    >
      <pre class="font-mono text-sm leading-relaxed overflow-x-auto" style="background: none; border: none; margin: 0; padding: 0;"><code><span style="color: var(--color-accent);"># Skill Name</span>

<span style="color: var(--color-accent);">## When to activate</span>
[Specific trigger conditions — be precise, not generic]

<span style="color: var(--color-accent);">## When NOT to use</span>
[Anti-patterns — when this skill is the wrong tool]

<span style="color: var(--color-accent);">## Instructions</span>
[The actual skill content — patterns, prompts, steps]

<span style="color: var(--color-accent);">## Example</span>
[At least one concrete example showing the skill in use]</code></pre>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Agent format -->
  <section
    class="border-t"
    style="border-color: var(--color-border); background-color: var(--color-bg-elevated);"
  >
    <div class="container-page py-16">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight mb-3">Agent file format</h2>
      <p class="mb-8 text-sm max-w-2xl" style="color: var(--color-muted);">
        Every file in <code class="text-xs px-1 py-0.5 rounded" style="background-color: var(--color-muted-bg);">agents/</code> uses this structure.
        Model guidance and a tool subset are required — "all tools" is not acceptable.
      </p>
      <div
        class="rounded-lg p-6"
        style="background-color: var(--color-muted-bg); border: 1px solid var(--color-border);"
      >
        <pre class="font-mono text-sm leading-relaxed overflow-x-auto" style="background: none; border: none; margin: 0; padding: 0;"><code><span style="color: var(--color-accent);"># Agent Name</span>

<span style="color: var(--color-accent);">## Purpose</span>
[One sentence — what domain or task this agent owns]

<span style="color: var(--color-accent);">## Model guidance</span>
[Haiku / Sonnet / Opus — and why]

<span style="color: var(--color-accent);">## Tools</span>
[Specific tool subset this agent should use — not all tools]

<span style="color: var(--color-accent);">## When to delegate here</span>
[Trigger conditions for spawning this agent]

<span style="color: var(--color-accent);">## Example use case</span>
[Concrete example]</code></pre>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Quality bar -->
  <section class="container-page py-16">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight mb-8">Quality bar</h2>
    <div class="grid gap-8 md:grid-cols-2">
      <div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold mb-4">Skills</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm" style="color: var(--color-muted);">
          <li class="flex gap-2"><span style="color: var(--color-accent);">+</span> Clear "When to activate" with specific trigger conditions</li>
          <li class="flex gap-2"><span style="color: var(--color-accent);">+</span> "When NOT to use" with at least one anti-pattern</li>
          <li class="flex gap-2"><span style="color: var(--color-accent);">+</span> At least one concrete, runnable example</li>
          <li class="flex gap-2"><span style="color: var(--color-accent);">+</span> References real Claude Code features — not generic LLM advice</li>
          <li class="flex gap-2"><span style="color: var(--color-accent);">+</span> Tested in at least one real session</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold mb-4">Agents</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm" style="color: var(--color-muted);">
          <li class="flex gap-2"><span style="color: var(--color-accent);">+</span> Specifies a tool subset (not all tools)</li>
          <li class="flex gap-2"><span style="color: var(--color-accent);">+</span> Model guidance with reasoning (Haiku / Sonnet / Opus)</li>
          <li class="flex gap-2"><span style="color: var(--color-accent);">+</span> Concrete example use case</li>
        </ul>
        <h3 class="font-semibold mt-8 mb-4">What gets rejected</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm" style="color: var(--color-muted);">
          <li class="flex gap-2"><span style="color: var(--color-subtle);">−</span> Duplicates an existing file without clear improvement</li>
          <li class="flex gap-2"><span style="color: var(--color-subtle);">−</span> Placeholder or "coming soon" sections</li>
          <li class="flex gap-2"><span style="color: var(--color-subtle);">−</span> Generic LLM advice instead of Claude Code specifics</li>
          <li class="flex gap-2"><span style="color: var(--color-subtle);">−</span> Application code (this repo is docs and config only)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- PR flow -->
  <section
    class="border-y"
    style="background-color: var(--color-bg-elevated); border-color: var(--color-border);"
  >
    <div class="container-page py-16">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight mb-8">Submitting a PR</h2>
      <div class="grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-5">
        {[
          { step: "1", title: "Fork and branch", desc: 'Fork the repo and create a branch: git checkout -b add/your-skill-name' },
          { step: "2", title: "Add your file", desc: "One markdown file, correct subdirectory, correct format. Check README.md for the directory map." },
          { step: "3", title: "Note translations", desc: "If you added a new English guide, note in the PR description which translations are needed (FR, DE, NL, ES)." },
          { step: "4", title: "Open a PR", desc: 'Title like: "add: FastAPI skill" or "fix: token-optimization guide". No squash required.' },
          { step: "5", title: "Fill the description", desc: "What it is, why it's useful, how you tested it. That's the full bar." },
        ].map((item) => (
          <div>
            <div
              class="inline-flex items-center justify-center w-9 h-9 rounded-md mb-4 text-sm font-semibold"
              style="background-color: var(--color-accent-soft); color: var(--color-accent);"
            >
              {item.step}
            </div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold mb-2 text-sm">{item.title}</h3>
            <p class="text-sm" style="color: var(--color-muted);">{item.desc}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Translations -->
  <section class="container-page py-16">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight mb-3">Translating existing content</h2>
    <p class="mb-6 text-sm max-w-2xl" style="color: var(--color-muted);">
      Translation PRs are welcome. Keep all code blocks, file paths, and technical
      terms in English — only prose translates.
    </p>
    <div
      class="rounded-lg p-6"
      style="background-color: var(--color-muted-bg); border: 1px solid var(--color-border);"
    >
      <pre class="font-mono text-sm leading-relaxed overflow-x-auto" style="background: none; border: none; margin: 0; padding: 0;"><code><span style="color: var(--color-muted);"># Copy the English source</span>
cp guides/getting-started.md guides/fr/getting-started.md

<span style="color: var(--color-muted);"># PR title format</span>
translate: getting-started guide (French)</code></pre>
    </div>
    <p class="mt-4 text-sm" style="color: var(--color-muted);">
      Supported languages: English (primary) · French (<code class="text-xs px-1 py-0.5 rounded" style="background-color: var(--color-muted-bg);">fr/</code>) · German (<code class="text-xs px-1 py-0.5 rounded" style="background-color: var(--color-muted-bg);">de/</code>) · Dutch (<code class="text-xs px-1 py-0.5 rounded" style="background-color: var(--color-muted-bg);">nl/</code>) · Spanish (<code class="text-xs px-1 py-0.5 rounded" style="background-color: var(--color-muted-bg);">es/</code>)
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section
    class="border-t"
    style="border-color: var(--color-border); background-color: var(--color-bg-elevated);"
  >
    <div class="container-page py-16">
      <div class="max-w-xl">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight mb-3">Ready to contribute?</h2>
        <p class="text-sm mb-6" style="color: var(--color-muted);">
          Read the full skill authoring guide, then open a PR. Questions go in GitHub
          Discussions — not issues.
        </p>
        <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-3">
          <a href="/guides/skill-authoring/" class="btn-primary">Skill authoring guide</a>
          <a
            href="https://github.com/Claudients/Claudient"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener"
            class="btn-ghost"
          >
            Fork on GitHub
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
